RTX 3090 / 4090 

NVIDIA A100 / H100 (Data Center Grade) 

Processor (CPU) 

Intel i9 / AMD Ryzen 9 / EPYC 

Memory (RAM) 

32GB minimum (64–128GB recommended for CT datasets) 

High-Speed SSD Storage 

NVMe SSD, 1TB+ for fast dataset loading 

Cooling System 

It is necessary due to heavy GPU workloads. [8] 

B. Deep Learning Servers 

For large-scale hospitals or research environments. 

DGX Server (NVIDIA DGX A100/DGX H100) 
Multi-GPU supercomputer for AI training. 

Cluster Computing Setup 
Multiple nodes connected through high-speed network (InfiniBand). [9] 

 

4. Preprocessing & Feature Extraction Hardware 

